{"title_page": "Paul Wahlberg", "text_new": "{{short description|American chef}}\n{{refimprove|date=July 2018}}\n{{infobox person\n|name = Paul Wahlberg\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1964|3|20}}\n|birth_place = [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n|occupation = Chef\n|known = Owner of [[Wahlburgers]]\n|relatives = [[Mark Wahlberg]] <br> [[Donnie Wahlberg]] <br> [[Robert Wahlberg]]\n|children = 2\n}}\n'''Paul A. Wahlberg''' (born March 20, 1964) is an American chef, actor and a reality TV star. With his brothers [[Mark Wahlberg|Mark]] and [[Donnie Wahlberg|Donnie]], he runs the dining burger restaurant and bar [[Wahlburgers]] and stars in the reality television also titled ''[[Wahlburgers (TV series)|Wahlburgers]]''.\n\n==Background==\nBorn in [[Boston]] to Alma and Donald Wahlberg, he is the fifth of nine children and the first of his siblings to graduate from high school.<ref>{{cite web |title=A&E bio |url=https://www.aetv.com/shows/wahlburgers/cast/paul-wahlberg |website=A&E |accessdate=26 July 2018}}</ref>  His brother [[Mark Wahlberg]] is a convicted violent racist for [[hate crimes]] who later went on to produce the sexist and racist TV series [[Entourage]].<ref>{{cite web|title=https://www.wired.com/2015/04/binge-guide-entourage/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Back In The Day: Marky Mark's Rap Sheet|url=http://www.thesmokinggun.com/file/back-day-marky-marks-rap-sheet-0?page=8|page=8|website=The Smoking Gun|accessdate=May 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420163859/http://www.thesmokinggun.com/file/back-day-marky-marks-rap-sheet-0?page=8|archive-date=April 20, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAs a child, he was interested in watching cooking shows like ''[[The Galloping Gourmet]]''.  He decided to become a chef when he was 17.<ref name=\"Juliet\">{{cite news |last1=Pennington |first1=Juliet |title=A Visit to Alma\u2019s Kitchen with Chef Paul Wahlberg |url=http://newenglandliving.tv/a-visit-to-almas-kitchen-with-chef-paul-wahlberg/ |accessdate=10 February 2019 |publisher=New England Living |date=July 18, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nPaul found a love for the culinary industry working for Joseph's catering, ran by the Calapa family of Braintree, MA. After high school, he worked at several restaurants, including The Charles Hotel, The Four Seasons and Bridgeman's in [[Hull, Massachusetts]], where he served as executive chef for nine years.<ref name=\"Alma\">{{cite web |title=Chef Paul Wahlberg |url=https://www.almanovehingham.com/chef-paul-wahlberg/ |website=Alma Nove |accessdate=26 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nMarried, Wahlberg lives in [[Hingham, Massachusetts]].  He has two children.<ref name=\"VIP lounge\">{{cite news |last1=Pennington |first1=Juliet |title=The VIP Lounge with Paul Wahlberg, executive chef at Wahlburger\u2019s |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/food-dining/2018/04/04/the-vip-lounge-with-paul-wahlberg-executive-chef-wahlburger/lWGCCtxAYBNxi0EW7LCtOJ/story.html |accessdate=10 February 2019 |publisher=Boston Globe |date=April 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Wahlberg family}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wahlberg, Paul}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:American restaurateurs]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Dorchester, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Wahlberg family]]\n[[Category:People from Hingham, Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:American people of Swedish descent]]\n\n{{Chef-bio-stub}}\n{{US-tv-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American chef}}\n{{refimprove|date=July 2018}}\n{{infobox person\n|name = Paul Wahlberg\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1964|3|20}}\n|birth_place = [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n|occupation = Chef\n|known = Owner of [[Wahlburgers]]\n|relatives = [[Mark Wahlberg]] <br> [[Donnie Wahlberg]] <br> [[Robert Wahlberg]]\n|children = 2\n}}\n'''Paul A. Wahlberg''' (born March 20, 1964) is an American chef, actor and a reality TV star. With his brothers [[Mark Wahlberg|Mark]] and [[Donnie Wahlberg|Donnie]], he runs the 